{"type":"message","id":"6dd48fbf","parentId":"3d0b3fcd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:43:57.946Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ltt9mapmaz5u_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 094322\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. The most concrete pending item is the TIC Experiment - implementing Temporal Invariance Compression on pulse logs\r\n2. This is the \"NEXT ACTION\" listed under Phase 1 Advancement\r\n3. The goal is to test on last 20 pulse logs and measure classification accuracy\r\n\r\nThe most logical action right now would be to either:\r\n1. Implement the TIC classifier\r\n2. Create a script to analyze the pulse logs\r\n3. Update the research document with a specification for TIC\r\n\r\nSince the next action explicitly calls for implementing TIC on `logs/pulse_*.md` files, I should create a script or specification for this. Let me implement a TIC classifier or at least a script that can analyze pulse logs for invariance.\r\n\r\nI could create:\r\n- A PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns\r\n- A specification document for the TIC experiment\r\n- Actually implement the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC analysis script that can be run on the pulse logs. This would be the concrete next step.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the structure, I should probably create a script that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Looks for invariant (persistent across pulses) vs variant (changing) content\r\n3. Tests prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me create a PowerShell script for this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the explicit next action, but I need a working script to analyze pulse logs for invariant patterns and test prediction accuracy before I can validate against the success criteria.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic_analyzer.ps1` - a PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs to classify content as invariant (persistent across sessions) vs variant (changing), and tests next-pulse prediction using invariant-only context.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Analyzer - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant classification and prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$PulseCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Collect recent pulse logs\r\n$pulseLogs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $PulseCount\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"TIC Analyzer - Analyzing $($pulseLogs.Count) pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n# Extract content lines from each pulse\r\nfunction Get-PulseContent {\r\n    param([string]$Path)\r\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw\r\n    # Extract key-value pairs and headers\r\n    $lines = $content -split \"`n\" | Where-Object { $_ -match \"^\\[|^##|^\\w+:\" }\r\n    return $lines\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Build invariant set: items that appear in ALL pulses\r\n$allItems = @{}\r\nforeach ($log in $pulseLogs) {\r\n    $lines = Get-PulseContent $log.FullName\r\n    foreach ($line in $lines) {\r\n        $key = $line.Trim()\r\n        if ($allItems.ContainsKey($key)) {\r\n            $allItems[$key]++\r\n        } else {\r\n            $allItems[$key] = 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Invariant = appears in ALL pulses (100% persistence)\r\n$invariantThreshold = $pulseLogs.Count\r\n$invariants = $allItems.GetEnumerator() | \r\n    Where-Object { $_.Value -eq $invariantThreshold } |\r\n    Select-Object -ExpandProperty Key\r\n\r\n# Variant = appears in SOME but not ALL pulses\r\n$variants = $allItems.GetEnumerator() | \r\n    Where-Object { $_.Value -lt $invariantThreshold -and $_.Value -gt 1 } |\r\n    Select-Object -ExpandProperty Key\r\n\r\n# Unique = appears in only ONE pulse\r\n$uniques = $allItems.GetEnumerator() | \r\n    Where-Object { $_.Value -eq 1 } |\r\n    Select-Object -ExpandProperty Key\r\n\r\n# Calculate classification accuracy (invariants should predict persistent structure)\r\n$totalClassified = $invariants.Count + $variants.Count + $uniques.Count\r\n$classificationAccuracy = if ($totalClassified -gt 0) { \r\n    ($invariants.Count / $totalClassified) * 100 \r\n} else { 0 }\r\n\r\n# Test prediction: use invariants from pulses 1..N-1 to predict pulse N\r\n$predictionCorrect = 0\r\n$predictionTotal = 0\r\n\r\nif ($pulseLogs.Count -ge 2) {\r\n    for ($i = 1; $i -lt $pulseLogs.Count; $i++) {\r\n        $trainingSet = $pulseLogs[0..($i-1)]\r\n        $testPulse = $pulseLogs[$i]\r\n        \r\n        # Build invariant set from training\r\n        $trainItems = @{}\r\n        foreach ($log in $trainingSet) {\r\n            $lines = Get-PulseContent $log.FullName\r\n            foreach ($line in $lines) {\r\n                $key = $line.Trim()\r\n                if ($trainItems.ContainsKey($key)) { $trainItems[$key]++ } \r\n                else { $trainItems[$key] = 1 }\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        $trainInvariants = $trainItems.GetEnumerator() | \r\n            Where-Object { $_.Value -eq $trainingSet.Count } |\r\n            Select-Object -ExpandProperty Key\r\n        \r\n        # Check if test pulse contains these invariants\r\n        $testLines = Get-PulseContent $testPulse.FullName\r\n        foreach ($inv in $trainInvariants) {\r\n            if ($testLines -contains $inv) { $predictionCorrect++ }\r\n            $predictionTotal++\r\n        }\r\n   \r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:43:52"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1013,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 094322\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. The most concrete pending item is the TIC Experiment - implementing Temporal Invariance Compression on pulse logs\r\n2. This is the \"NEXT ACTION\" listed under Phase 1 Advancement\r\n3. The goal is to test on last 20 pulse logs and measure classification accuracy\r\n\r\nThe most logical action right now would be to either:\r\n1. Implement the TIC classifier\r\n2. Create a script to analyze the pulse logs\r\n3. Update the research document with a specification for TIC\r\n\r\nSince the next action explicitly calls for implementing TIC on `logs/pulse_*.md` files, I should create a script or specification for this. Let me implement a TIC classifier or at least a script that can analyze pulse logs for invariance.\r\n\r\nI could create:\r\n- A PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns\r\n- A specification document for the TIC experiment\r\n- Actually implement the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC analysis script that can be run on the pulse logs. This would be the concrete next step.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the structure, I should probably create a script that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Looks for invariant (persistent across pulses) vs variant (changing) content\r\n3. Tests prediction of next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me create a PowerShell script for this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the explicit next action, but I need a working script to analyze pulse logs for invariant patterns and test prediction accuracy before I can validate against the success criteria.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic_analyzer.ps1` - a PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs to classify content as invariant (persistent across